import React from 'react'
  import { MDXTag } from '@mdx-js/tag'
  import { Playground, PropsTable } from 'docz'
import VenueCardsScreen from './screens/VenueCardsScreen'
import { View, StyleSheet } from 'react-native'
import { colors } from '../constants'
import ApolloClient from 'apollo-boost'
import { ApolloProvider } from 'react-apollo'

export default ({components, ...props}) => <MDXTag name="wrapper"  components={components}>
<MDXTag name="h1" components={components} props={{"id":"venuecardsscreenjs-previously-venuecardsjs"}}>{`VenueCardsScreen.js (Previously VenueCards.js)`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"description"}}>{`Description`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`Previously known as 'VenueCards.js', this component is a screen that displays venue cards,
which includes an image, venue name, and venue neighborhood. Scrolling is vertical.
It grabs data from a GraphQL database and use Apollo to connect the two entities. The query
to grab over 60 venues worth of data includes venue id, venue name, venue description,
venue hoursText, neighborhood names, photo handles (part of a compressed image's url),
and category name.`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"properties"}}>{`Properties`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`Contains props passed from react-navigation and apollo's GraphQL query:`}</MDXTag>
<PropsTable of={VenueCardsScreen} />
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"requirements"}}>{`Requirements`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`Follow these steps to set up the environment (using the terminal):`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="ul" components={components}>
<MDXTag name="li" components={components} parentName="ul">
<MDXTag name="p" components={components} parentName="li">{`Install NVM (Node Version Manager) `}<MDXTag name="inlineCode" components={components} parentName="p">{`curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/creationix/nvm/v0.33.11/install.sh | bash`}</MDXTag></MDXTag>
</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="li" components={components} parentName="ul">
<MDXTag name="p" components={components} parentName="li">{`Run `}<MDXTag name="inlineCode" components={components} parentName="p">{`nvm install node`}</MDXTag>{` to install the latest version of node.`}</MDXTag>
</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="li" components={components} parentName="ul">
<MDXTag name="p" components={components} parentName="li">{`You must have the expo-cli to run this project. So run the command `}<MDXTag name="inlineCode" components={components} parentName="p">{`npm install -g expo-cli`}</MDXTag></MDXTag>
</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="li" components={components} parentName="ul">
<MDXTag name="p" components={components} parentName="li">{`Now, if you want to run an iphone emulator, an easy way to download it is to download XCode if you have a Mac.
If you want to run on an android emulator, the process is a bit longer but you'll just have to download Android Studio
and download an emulator from within there. If you choose to run and test on your mobile device, install the Expo app
from your Google play store or Apple App store.`}</MDXTag>
</MDXTag>
</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"how-to-run"}}>{`How to run`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`Create a folder to clone this repo to and cd into it. Run these commands on your terminal:`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="ul" components={components}>
<MDXTag name="li" components={components} parentName="ul">
<MDXTag name="p" components={components} parentName="li"><MDXTag name="inlineCode" components={components} parentName="p">{`git clone "https://github.com/pcooney10/rn-starter-edgar"`}</MDXTag></MDXTag>
</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="li" components={components} parentName="ul">
<MDXTag name="p" components={components} parentName="li"><MDXTag name="inlineCode" components={components} parentName="p">{`cd rn-starter-edgar`}</MDXTag></MDXTag>
</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="li" components={components} parentName="ul">
<MDXTag name="p" components={components} parentName="li"><MDXTag name="inlineCode" components={components} parentName="p">{`expo start`}</MDXTag></MDXTag>
</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="li" components={components} parentName="ul">
<MDXTag name="p" components={components} parentName="li">{`Now, depending on the emulator you want to to use, in the terminal press 1 of 3 options:`}</MDXTag>
</MDXTag>
</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="ol" components={components}>
<MDXTag name="li" components={components} parentName="ol">
<MDXTag name="p" components={components} parentName="li"><MDXTag name="inlineCode" components={components} parentName="p">{`i`}</MDXTag>{` to run on an iphone emulator you've installed on your PC`}</MDXTag>
</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="li" components={components} parentName="ol">
<MDXTag name="p" components={components} parentName="li"><MDXTag name="inlineCode" components={components} parentName="p">{`a`}</MDXTag>{` if you have an android emulator installed on your PC`}</MDXTag>
</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="li" components={components} parentName="ol">
<MDXTag name="p" components={components} parentName="li"><MDXTag name="inlineCode" components={components} parentName="p">{`e`}</MDXTag>{` to send a link to your phone via email or text.`}</MDXTag>
</MDXTag>
</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"basic-usage"}}>{`Basic Usage`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`Connect with GraphQL via Apollo and querie data that will be passed into this
component. Component is looking for venue.id, venue.name, venue.neighborhood.name, and
a venue.photos`}{`[0]`}{`.handle. The handle is then put at the end of a url string to
display an image.`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`This component passes its query down to the child component VenueDetailsScreen.js with
the help of React Navigation. Due to this, child component will be expecting
venue.address, venue.description, venue.hoursText, and venue.category.name so be
sure to query that as well.`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"ui"}}>{`UI`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`On a web browser, this will appear as a long list of venue cards. On a mobile
application, this component will have as many cards that could fit in a phone screen,
typically 4 at least, and the user will have to scroll down to view the rest of the list.`}</MDXTag>
